{"url": "https://www.ics.uci.edu/~dechter/courses/ics-275a/fall-99/slides/node192.html", "content": "<!DOCTYPE HTML PUBLIC \"-//W3O//DTD W3 HTML 2.0//EN\">\r\n<!Converted with LaTeX2HTML 95.1 (Fri Jan 20 1995) by Nikos Drakos (nikos@cbl.leeds.ac.uk), CBLU, University of Leeds >\r\n<HEAD>\r\n<TITLE> Command Line Arguments</TITLE>\r\n</HEAD>\r\n<BODY>\r\n<meta name=\"description\" value=\" Command Line Arguments\">\r\n<meta name=\"keywords\" value=\"umsroot\">\r\n<meta name=\"resource-type\" value=\"document\">\r\n<meta name=\"distribution\" value=\"global\">\r\n<P>\r\n <BR> <HR><A NAME=tex2html4561 HREF=\"node193.html\"><IMG ALIGN=BOTTOM ALT=\"next\" SRC=\"http://www.ecrc.de/eclipse/new_icons//next_motif.gif\"></A>   <A NAME=tex2html4559 HREF=\"node191.html\"><IMG ALIGN=BOTTOM ALT=\"up\" SRC=\"http://www.ecrc.de/eclipse/new_icons//up_motif.gif\"></A>   <A NAME=tex2html4553 HREF=\"node191.html\"><IMG ALIGN=BOTTOM ALT=\"previous\" SRC=\"http://www.ecrc.de/eclipse/new_icons//previous_motif.gif\"></A>      <A NAME=tex2html4563 HREF=\"node321.html\"><IMG ALIGN=BOTTOM ALT=\"index\" SRC=\"http://www.ecrc.de/eclipse/new_icons//index_motif.gif\"></A>   <BR>\r\n<B> Next:</B> <A NAME=tex2html4562 HREF=\"node193.html\"> Environment Variables</A>\r\n<B>Up:</B> <A NAME=tex2html4560 HREF=\"node191.html\"> Environment Access</A>\r\n<B> Previous:</B> <A NAME=tex2html4554 HREF=\"node191.html\"> Environment Access</A>\r\n<BR> <HR> <P>\r\n<H2><A NAME=SECTION001721000000000000000> Command Line Arguments</A></H2>\r\n<P>\r\nArguments provided on the UNIX command line are accessed by the builtins\r\n<A NAME=2889>&#160;</A>\r\n<A NAME=2890>&#160;</A>\r\n<A NAME=2891>&#160;</A>\r\n<b> argc/1</b> which gives the number of command line arguments (including\r\nthe command name itself) and <b> argv/2</b> which returns a requested positional\r\nargument in string form. The following example makes a list of all\r\ncommand line arguments:\r\n<blockquote> <PRE> collect_args(List) :-\r\n        argc(N),\r\n        collect_args(N, [], List).\r\n collect_args(0, List, List) :- !.\r\n collect_args(N, List0, List) :-\r\n        N1 is N-1,\r\n        argv(N1, Arg),\r\n        collect_args(N1, [Arg|List0], List).\r\n</PRE></blockquote><BR> <HR>\r\n<P><ADDRESS>\r\n<I>Micha Meier <BR>\r\nMon Mar  4 12:11:45 MET 1996</I>\r\n</ADDRESS>\r\n</BODY>\r\n", "encoding": "ascii"}